Serialized Form

  • Package edu.cpp.cs.cs141.prog_final

    • Class edu.cpp.cs.cs141.prog_final.GameEngine extends java.lang.Object implements Serializable

      serialVersionUID:
      -2496518892115630362L

      • Serialized Fields

        • briefcase

          Briefcase briefcase
          This field represents the briefcase in the game. When this is found, the game has been won. The briefcase is placed in the same coordinates of a room, but randomly.

        • bullet

          Bullet bullet
          This field represents a bullet from the Bullet class Bullet and will be used to give the player a bullet if he or she does not have one.

        • debugMode

          boolean debugMode
          This field is used to keep track of debug mode. When starting the game, debug mode will automatically be set to false. The player has a choice to use debug mode as on of the options. It will toggle debug mode without using up a turn.

        • grid

          Grid grid
          This field represents a grid from the Grid.java class Grid and calls the new object grid. This is used to create the board, and interact with it.

        • hardMode

          boolean hardMode
          This field is used as a game difficulty. Starting the game the player will have two options. One being easy mode, which will turn this value to false, and the other being hard mode, which will make the value of this boolean true. When this boolean is true, the player will be playing against ninjas that will be operated from a different method. Which increases the difficulty of the game.

        • invinc

          Invincibility invinc
          This field represents an invincibility item from the Invincibility class Invincibility and will grant the player a shield for five turns.

        • ninjas

          Ninja[] ninjas
          This field holds an array of Ninjas. The ninjas will be accessed using this array, and all interaction will be done through this field.

        • player

          Player player
          This field is the player object from the player Player class. This means the player is being held in the grid, moves based on the input from the User interface but is operated in the engine. Just like the ninja class, the player class is moved in the engine but the movement is based on what is inputted in the user interface when the method movePlayer is called.

        • radar

          Radar radar
          This field represents a radar item from the Radar class Radar that will grant the player with the location of the briefcase.

        • radarFound

          boolean radarFound
          This field is used to keep track of the radar. Starting the game will initialize its value to false and when the radarFound is turned to true. It will call a method in the item class and turn the isUsed field to true. As well as use up the item removing it from the grid and displaying the location of the briefcase.

        • rand

          java.util.Random rand
          This field of Random allows the object "rand" created from the imported java utility Random to randomize and move the positions of objects within the grid. The object "rand" will move the ninja with equal chance of moving in each direction.

    • Class edu.cpp.cs.cs141.prog_final.Grid extends java.lang.Object implements Serializable

      serialVersionUID:
      2229073517795270773L

      • Serialized Fields

        • board

          char[][] board
          This is the 2D array that represents the current positions of everything in the game. These positions are represented through characters, hence the 2D char array.

        • DIMENSION

          int DIMENSION
          The dimension of the board. Useful so that if this needs to change, each individual value will not have to be changed

        • light

          boolean[][] light
          This is the 2D array that represents the lighting of the grid. The grid is filled with boolean values, either true, which represents an illuminated spot, or false, which represents a dark spot.

    • Class edu.cpp.cs.cs141.prog_final.beings.Player extends LivingBeing implements Serializable

      serialVersionUID:
      1944010931443879594L

      • Serialized Fields

        • bullet

          int bullet
          This field represents the amount of bullets that the player has in their gun. The max amount of bullets a gun can carry is one. Initially 1, will decrease by 1 whenever a shot is taken. If the player has no bullets, then no shot can be taken.

        • lives

          int lives
          This field represents the amount of lives that the player has. The player starts off with three lives, so this value is initially 3. If the player loses all 3 lives, the game is over, and the player has lost the game.

        • shield

          boolean shield
          This field is used to show if the player has the invincibility power up used. It will also have an initial value of false so that the turn does not start counting down.
